<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880616-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Harsco Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HSC GM </CO><TEXT>   Harsco Corp., Camp Hill, Pa., said its BMY division formed a 50-50 joint venture with a General Motors Corp. unit to compete for Army tactical-vehicle contracts.    Harsco said the new venture, to be called Tactical Truck Corp., will provide a concept design proposal for submission to the Army in July. The Army is expected to award contracts to as many as three companies in September for 15 prototype vehicles.    Harsco is a diversified industrial company that makes 21 classes of products and services, mainly for defense, industrial, commercial and construction industries. Detroit-based GM is an auto maker. </TEXT></DOC>